caption: Great food

Absolutely incredible. And the best Burger I've ever had in my life. I love going out to restaurants. I've been to restaurants from the Midwest, to New York City, to LA, Miami, and Vegas. Cheap restaurants and expensive restaurants. But I can say this without reservation: Their Wagyu Burger was truly the best burger I had ever had in my lifetime. And I'm a hamburger guy. I truly could not believe it when I bit into that burger. I can't tell you just how badly you need to try that thing. The atmosphere was so peaceful, calming, yet still fun. The lighting was wonderful. It's in a great location. The food is amazing. And the staff were so nice and went out of their way to help. West Lafayette needed more sit down and eat places, and this might just be the best one in town. But it certainly has the best Burger.
Great atmosphere,  Great service, Personable Staff,  Food is amazing!! Craft cocktails bring us back again and again.  Wish we could keep 8/11 a secret so we can always get right in.

Three plates in our party, Mussels $18, Mushroom Bolognese $18, and tomahawk ribeye the evening special.  The mussels and broth were fantastic.  Mushroom Bolognese tasted very little of mushrooms but of a cup of sugar instead, similar to the sweetness of SpaghettiOs when I was a child.  The steak was fantastic.  I could not say a bad word until the bill.  Entrees at 8Eleven range from $18-$48.  Imagine my surprise when I received a bill for a $140 steak.  Never a warning by the server as to the price of the special before it was ordered.  I bear joint responsibility for not asking, however I will not dine there again, unless someone else is buying.  Warning to others, ask the price of the special(s)!

Had Brooke as our server, being my first time visiting Purdue as a prospective student, she was not only helpful but told me of some amazing places to visit on campus and why Purdue is a great choice. Aside from the amazing service the appetizers we had at the bar were delicious, and would recommend to anyone in the area.

The Bacon Old-Fashion is Excellent as was the Roasted Bone Marrow. The Frisee Salad was expertly done with the perfect balance of dressing and toppings. The menu is definitely more expensive than most places in West Lafayette but This is definitely worth a return visit in the future!

First time trying this newish spot in town. Placed an order online for pick-up. The place was bustling on a Saturday night. Loved the ambience - not too noisy, mood lighting, decor is gorgeous! The bar and restaurant area are separate. There is also a place to to grab coffee/snacks if that's all you're in the mood for.  We tried the following from their dinner menu: 1) Burrata Cheese with apricot mostarda, truffle honey, marcona almond, grilled rustic bread. The combination of the cheese + apricot is delicious! 2) Shoestring fries 3) Wild Mushroom Bolognese - I really enjoyed this dish. Not usually one to go for pasta, but this was definitely worth it. Very flavourful. 4) Mille feuille - very tasty. The pastry was a little drier than what I'm used to, but I'd still recommend it.  Portions are good. We shared the above between two people.  The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because there aren't a lot (if at all any) vegetarian or vegan options on the menu, except for some salad and side items.
Food is great but a number of the staff are very rude.

Wow!! Great atmosphere, service, food, and drinks. The escargot, crab croquettes, prime rib French dip, and wild mushrooms (side dish) were all made and presented fantastically. Great place for a special occasion.
Great meal. Great atmosphere. Our server, Grace, was the best. Get the keylime pie.  You will thank me.
Incredible food, atmosphere, and service. The perfect spot for an upscale dinner or special occasion.
Amazing food, atmosphere and cocktails. We  tried the Braised beef and would definitely order it again. The different old fashioneds are worth trying.
Good burgers
First time dining here and Zach made it a wonderful experience! Will absolutely come again!
Great tasting food.

Best place to eat hands down for miles in our own backyard!  Best food, drinks, desserts, everything beyond all expectations!  Ambiance, wait staff from start to finish was amazing!  For every special or any occasion highly recommend.  No need to look further for the best place to go!  Go 8ELEVEN

We had a lovely birthday dinner. The special, a 29 oz tomahawk steak, was cooked perfectly. The best part of the evening was the service. Our server, Grace, was perfectly attentive, helpful, and made the night memorable. Will return!
Great food, service, and ambiance
Great experience.  Wonderful food. Perfect service. Artisan cocktails to rival any. Thanks for taking cate of us Grace!
Amazing food, fantastic service! Just what we need in West Lafayette. Grace, our server, was wonderful and gave great recommendations. This place is a must!

We had a wonderful experience from beginning to end. Our server Grace was not only helpful and attentive, but very caring. It was one of the best meals and experiences we’ve had in a long time. We are from the east coast dropping off our daughter at Purdue so our stay at the Union Hotel and dinner tonight was such a great and much needed experience. Thank you Eight Eleven! We will be back. Can’t wait.
Food was done to perfection. Our server Grace was ver professional and made sure that everything met our expectations! The Key Lime Pie is Out of the World
Very friendly staff!

What a very special place to observe a special occasion! We came over to Indiana today in order to watch a movie. Since the hour was later, we chose to head into West Lafayette for dinner and opted to stay the night instead. So thankful we did just that, and we found 8Eleven Bistro. The food was some of the very best we have had in the 25+ years of our happy marriage that has taken us to over 40 states. The food is THAT good! Thank you so much for the welcome we received, the crab croquettes , the delectable crunchy fresh salads, and the memorable braised beef and pan seared chicken, to the magical Key Lime Pie. It was all world-class, first-rate, five-star worthy: however you wish to classify some of the best food you can find anywhere. Love this place and will be back again!
Visited for a birthday celebration - phenomenal drinks, food, service, and atmosphere. Loved it!
Great vibe, food and service!
Excellent food
Top notch dining experience! The oysters and halibut were delicious and service was really great. We'll be back!
The food and service were wonderful.
Service and quality of the food was outstanding!! Very well done.
This is an amazing place.  Excellent meal with exceptional service.  Very extensive drink menu. Lots of attention to every little detail.  Don't miss this place.  I would give 6 stars if I  could.

I had an amazing experience at 8Eleven Bistro! Not only were the staff very friendly and attentive, but I also felt very comfortable, which can be difficult to achieve during COVID-19. The warmly lit environment took their bourbon display to the next level; providing that classic aesthetic that could fool you into thinking you were in Louisville or Nashville.  I highly recommend the burrata cheese appetizer and the bread pudding; they were absolutely delicious. If you like seafood then definitely order the scallops, but if that's not your style, the menu has a variety of other enticing options. As 8Eleven Bistro evolves, I would love to see more vegetarian entrées on the dinner menu. Nevertheless, I am looking forward to my return, and I highly recommend 8Eleven to everybody!

This restaurant was phenomenal! From the drinks, to the appetizers, main course and dessert.... we loved everything we had. We can’t wait to come back.  Only suggestion, the salad greens had a wonderful dressing. Something added on the salad would give it some more pizzazz.

High end cuisine done exceptionally well.  Service is impeccable from students who will restore your optimism in the next generation.  A great homage and addition to the fine traditions of Purdue.  Bravo!

Went here for Brunch on Sunday and it was AMAZING. I had the crepes and a mimosa, and they were delicious!! The ambience and decor are super cute and inviting. They also have a bar and a coffee bar. I cannot wait to try their lunch and dinner options! I will definitely be back.

BRAVO! This restaurant is yet another crown jewel for the Purdue campus at West Lafayette. I am so proud of everything about this venue. The historical lime arches, the stained glass windows and the original wood panels have been preserved in the most tasteful way for this eminent five-star restaurant. The warm leather, and the soft aroma of it, combined with contemporary fixtures and dropped curved wooden ceiling beams modernized this space in such a wonderful way while keeping the character of rich history. The ambiance at the adjacent Boiler Up bar matched the awe we felt at 8Eleven.  And the FOOD! The feature this night was Steak Oscar with the most tender, center-cut filet cooked to perfection, the freshest crab in generous portion and house made creamy hollandaise served on tender, not stringy, asparagus. All 4 of us who ordered this agreed we have never had better!  Our server, Aaron, was an attentive consummate professional who catered to our every need and left us wanting for nothing.  There is no better place to create a special memory, as we were doing for my son's 21st birthday.  The renovations were worth the wait! I told my husband I am glad we got to experience it now because when the word gets out, we'll be hard pressed to ever get a table again.  Worth every penny!

This is a very nice place with a great vibe. The food was really great, we had a great time. The staff was really friendly but our waiter was really distracted. We did not get forks, I did not get a knife and some other minor details, but the friendliness and the food made up of any small mistakes. I highly recommend this place. The best in West Lafayette, IN….so far.
This was our first time coming here tonight. Food was really good!!! Customer service was top notch! Hannah, our server, was great! Highly recommend trying this place:)
Justin was fabulous. He was polite, kind and helpful!
I Love it !! Jordan is the best , I recommend it!
Jordan is an outstanding server and Great food! BOILER UP 🚂

Jordan was amazing as our server. Offered the best recommendations for every course of our meal. We were bummed they were out of the burrata appetizer but he came in to save the day with the amazing crab croquets. My halibut was to die for as well. The key lime pie he recommended was amazing! Would recommend this place to anyone and a much needed place on Purdue’s campus!
Excellent service and food. Jordan was very helpful and kind.
The food and drinks were very good. I loved the key lime pie. My bartender was very nice. Good service.
We had a great experience! Our server Amanda was very nice and the food was delicious! We will be back!
Waiter was excellent and knowledgeable. Food was very good!
Food was delicious!
Ambiance galore! Can’t wait to come back. Servers very friendly and polite, but forgot to offer salt and pepper, waited, but had to go look for her! Then the pepper grinder was completely empty. ☹️

The flavors of this place continue to amaze. As a vegetarian, it is sometimes hard to find places that have adequate options paired with quality flavor and portions. I had been here for dinner and wanted to try their brunch. I gotta say, whatta treat. The mushroom and spinach egg white omelet was incredible and paired with one of their specialty brunch drinks was spectacular.  (The sunrise if any of you are curious).  Additionally the wait staff has always been very kind, very knowledgeable about a variety of topics and understanding. I had Grace as my server and she was a class act. I would absolutely recommend that you request her when making a reservation.  While I wish they had a couple more options for vegetarians/alternative ways to make other dishes vegetarian, the options the have are nothing divine. I would 100% recommend coming here for a weekend brunch. An excellent experience.
The hotel is very cool, love the quirks. The staff is friendly and helpful. Definitely would stay again!

Hands down the best service, food and atmosphere I ha e ever experienced. The staff goes above and beyond to make sure you are enjoying yourself. This is the first time I've been here since the Union renovation and I cannot believe how amazing this restaurant looks and feels. I will be bringing all my clients here for dinner and drinks in the future.
Absolutely amazing food and the experience was PERFECTION!!  Special shout out to our server, Hannah, who was fantastic!!!  We WILL come back!!!
Celebrated my birthday here and it was perfect! Hannah did a great job as our server - friendly and efficient.  Loved the braised beef and the beet & apple salad! We will be back!
Hannah did an amazing job and kept everything efficient. She and the rest of the staff was very apologetic for the long wait past the reservation.
I had Hannah as our server. She was awesome! She got everything we need at the right time. Also, she was on top of everything!! I had a great experience!!
The food was excellent, and the head chef stopped by our table t walk us through the menu and answer any questions we had
The food is amazing and the staff was great. The manager had great recommendations.
The food was AMAZING and we loved our server Rylan!

Everything was amazing! The food was really good and pretty, and the drinks were good! I went on a date here with my boyfriend and our server, Hannah, was so nice to us! I would definitely ask for her. The chef and manager also talked to us at our table - the staff is soo friendly. Would recommend!
Hannah was a great and attentive waitress. Food was great!

What a great place for an upscale date night. Very modern feel and amazing food. More pricey than most places in Lafayette and worth every penny! Hannah was our server and so great navigating the menu for us and bringing everything timely. Can’t wait to come back!
Awesome, great experience, Hannah was our server and did an excellent job!   Very flavorful dishes.

This place is a hidden gem. I know it sounds like cliché, but 5 stars are truly not enough. If your son or daughter happens to attend Purdue you absolutely must take them here the next time you visit. We ordered Gulf Shrimp Cocktail, Roasted Bone Marrow and Grilled Tuna Nicoise as appetizers. Deliciously impressive, especially the bone marrow which was a new discovery for us. Main courses were Braised Beef and Truffled Spaghetti. The beef was amazing, but the real surprise were the Spaghetti. I am born and raised in Italy, so I have very high standards when it comes to pasta and this dish was absolutely perfect. It was like being in a restaurant back in Rome. Really. Desserts were Mille Feuille and Profiteroles. Do not order the Mille Feuille, otherwise you will ask for two more. You have been warned. Profiteroles too were out of this world. You absolutely have to try this place. You won't regret it. Ah, one more thing....I really enjoyed their 8 Eleven Signature drink. One-of-a-kind for my taste.
The service was very good. They brought us lots of things to try as we were waiting for our food. Our server Hannah was also very nice!

Highly recommend - classy atmosphere, incredible artisan French/American food, attentive service. Save the kids for your favorite pizza place. This is definitely made for date night, dinner with friends or business associates, special occasions, or just because you want to go to a place to unwind and feel some culture. Every menu item/drink we’ve had has been perfect, but personally recommend the crab appetizer, scallops, Caesar salad, key lime pie.
Food and service were both wonderful! Steak was cooked perfectly and the truffled spaghetti was divine. This will be our go-to for special Purdue celebrations! Highly recommend.
Food was delicious. Rylan, our server, was absolutely amazing. Great atmosphere.

My experience at 8eleven was outstanding all thanks to my waiter, Rylan. He was an absolute pleasure and made my experience all that much better. The food was delectable and reasonably priced. 5/5 would return in a heart beat.

We had the most wonderful anniversary dinner date there this past week! They even gifted us champagne and dessert on the house! Highly recommend One of the best new places in west Lafayette/Lafayette! Top notch food, great atmosphere, and excellent service by our server Grace!
Fantastic food- probably the best bistro food in the Lafayette area.  Our server, Hannah, was wonderful- personal, professional, and attentive.
Exceptional service from Hannah!! She gave great recommendations and knew the menu very well. Food was great. Overall, a wonderful dining experience!!
I've been to my fair share of great places to eat and this place can hold it's own.

This is the go to spot for all things Purdue. Whether you’re grabbing a drink or a quick lunch on campus, you will not be disappointed.  The Bush Creek Ranch burger.... OMG!  Thank you Rylan for your hospitality and expertise about the menu!  If you are in near or around Purdue you need to check this place out!

Tonight was my second visit to 8Eleven in one week. Such good food, great atmosphere, wonderful service. I think it's probably the best date night/ladies night restaurant in town. I had the scallops the first visit and the cheeseburger the second visit. So so good. Highly recommend.
Terrific service, excellent food! We really enjoyed our getaway here and will definitely be back.
Food was delicious and service exceptional. Our server, Lucy, was very professional and caring, her recommendations on the menu spot on.
Delicious food, coffee and drinks! Great atmosphere
Hannah is amazing. The best person to have Emma shadow! Hannah is personable, fun, and super nice! Will definitely be coming back

We came to 8Eleven for our first night out since the pandemic started and it did not disappoint! The drink menu is amazing!!! Best drinks in town! Our server Jessica was fabulous! Friendly and offered lots of great suggestions! We will definitely be back!

8Eleven is one of the trendiest new bistros in West Lafayette! We had a phenomenal experience here! If you visit, make sure to ask for Hannah S. as your server. Her awesome recommendations helped us pick the perfect entrees. Overall great experience.

I took my wife for a date night and we enjoyed the food and drinks so much we returned the following week! Everything we tried was amazing. We highly recommend the cheese board, French onion soup, burger (possibly best I’ve had),  and my new favorite drink of all time is the bacon old fashioned! Bar service was extremely slow but overall we still throw them five stars!
Amazing restaurant. The atmosphere is great, service is so friendly and the food is the best in Lafayette!  I would definitely recommend if you are in the area.
The food was great. Hannah did a great job taking care of us. She made sure our glasses were never empty.
Drink recommendations were very good as was the service. Campbell was excellent!

The atmosphere was beautiful. Very quaint and clean. My husband and I shared an appetizer and a salad and we both got a main course. We had more than enough to eat and everything was delicious! I would come again!

Great ambiance. The craft cocktails are delicious (I has the watermelon mule). The food was delicious and very fairly priced. I was greeted with friendly faces and 2 different managers checked on me and thanked me for coming in. I will definitely be back.
